    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.8.9" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ENOS A. MILLS
                        <lb/>
                    LONGS PEAK, COLORADO</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>July 5, 1921.</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                            <addrLine>Branson, Missouri.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am glad to have the material sent and shall appreciate anything else on which you can lay hands. I should be pleased to have a copy of your <title>"Divine Enchantment"</title>. I should also be glad if you can tell me of any other especially good newspaper articles, giving me the name and date, also the address of Martha Foote Crow.</p>
                
                <p>For the past five years I have given at least one address concerning your work and have repeatedly commended you to editors. My plan now is to try to get one or more feature writers to have something concerning you and a little later to have something myself. I cannot now say just what or where.</p>
                
                <p>At any rate, you are unquestionably on the right track and I consider your work a distinct contribution to the appreciation of real things and an inspiration to everyone.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very truly yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Enos A. Mills</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
